RE: How do I deal with shame and guilt? You're a brave man, first... well I don't know how difficult it'd be for you but for me stripping on cam has exactly 0% chance of happening, and second for having the honest to gods giant sized balls to post here. She must have been satisfied anyway You have no reason to feel shame or guilt.
I am however rather delighted by your admission that in a previous life you would have gone to Jesus with something like this I love humans PS: It only happened recently. You'll forget it soon. Major part of feeling shame is feeling *there's something bad about me, something wrong with me, normal people don't do these kinds of things*. Am I right? Well. Normal people do do those kinds of things. Every single person who is the same age or older than you has been in plenty of horrible embarrassing situations of a similar level of indignity. So don't sweat it. We won't judge you.
PPS: If she's someone you know it's more of a pain. She's the one who made it awkward though. OTOH if she's still friendly realise that she may have just chickened out, girls also have a hard time with things like that, it takes courage from them too - if she got cold feet she probably feels bad about it herself.
